The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Rs 1.2 lakh for each India player

New Delhi: The 20-member Indian squad which won the SAFF Cup in Karachi would get cash rewards amounting to Rs 1,20,000 each, the All India Football Federation (AIFF) said on Sunday. 

Out of the winners prize of Rs 20 lakh, half would be equally distributed among the players which comes to Rs 50,000 per player, AIFF president Priya Ranjan Das Munshi said, adding that the federation would also give each player a bonus of Rs 70,000 for the title triumph. 

This would work as an incentive for our players to keep up the good performance leading up to the Doha Asian Games in December next year, the AIFF chief told reporters at Football House, the federations new headquarters, which would be functional from early next year. 

However, coach Syed Nayeemuddin would not get any part of the package. The coach is getting a monthly salary while the players do not have a fixed income, Das Munshi said. 

Das Munshi also hinted at contracts system for the players on the lines of the one adopted by the Board of Control for Cricket in India. 

The players would be divided into saffron, green and white groups, based on the number of internationals played and the number of goals scored, he said. 

Meanwhile, Dempo midfielder Climax Lawrence was adjudged the Player of the Year. The former Salgaocar and East Bengal medio, played a crucial role in Goa winning the Santosh Trophy this year. S. Venkatesh of Mahindra United won the award last year. 

10-team NFL 

Meanwhile, notwithstanding the pressure from the sides relegated in the National Football League top tier, the championship would remain a 10-team affair in the next season, Das Munshi insisted. 

Several teams approached the AIFF with a request to include them in the top division based on their performances in the Federation Cup. 

But the federation has decided to stick to its decision of having a 10-team competition, he said. (PTI) 




